Bestselling author Arthur C. Brooks will discuss and sign his new book, From Strength to Strength: Finding Success, Happiness and Deep Purpose in the Second Half of Life, at 3 p.m. April 21 at Oxford Exchange, 420 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Tickets $5 at oxfordexchange.com/pages/calendar. Award-winning author Robert Macomber will discuss his latest book, Code of Honor: A Novel of RADM Peter Wake, USN, in the 1904-1905 Russo-Japanese War, with author Ward Larsen at 7 p.m. April 21 at Tombolo Books, 2153 First Ave. S, St. Petersburg. Free; RSVP at tombolobooks.com/events. Tampa Bay Times staff writer Kristen Hare will be in conversation with former Times staffer and radio show host Ernest Hooper about the new third edition of her travel book 100 Things to Do In Tampa Bay Before You Die at 7 p.m. April 22 at Tombolo Books, 2153 First Ave. S, St. Petersburg. Free; RSVP at tombolobooks.com/events. Kristen Hare will be in conversation with Times columnist Stephanie Hayes about 100 Things to Do In Tampa Bay Before You Die at 3:30 p.m. April 24 at Oxford Exchange, 420 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Tickets $5 at oxfordexchange.com/pages/calendar. Book Talk is a listing of in-person author appearances in the Tampa Bay area in the coming week. To place an item in Book Talk, send author’s name, book title, appearance time, date, venue name and address, admission cost (if any) and a contact phone number to cbancroft@tampabay.com, with “Book Talk” in the subject line. Deadline is 14 days before publication.